.TH OPENDOOR 1 "May 2026" "OpenDoor 5.13.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
opendoor \- web directory discovery and reconnaissance scanner
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B opendoor
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B opendoor
.BI --host " URL"
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B opendoor
.BI --hostlist " FILE"
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B opendoor
.B --stdin
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
OpenDoor is a Python CLI scanner for authorized web reconnaissance,
directory discovery, subdomain enumeration, fingerprint detection, WAF
detection, controlled header-bypass probing, response filtering, reporting,
and transport-based scanning workflows.
.PP
Use OpenDoor only on systems you own or have explicit permission to test.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BI --host " URL"
Scan a single target host.
.TP
.BI --hostlist " FILE"
Read targets from a file, one target per line.
.TP
.B --stdin
Read targets from standard input, one target per line.
.TP
.BI -w ", " --wordlist " FILE"
Use a custom wordlist.
.TP
.BI -t ", " --threads " NUMBER"
Set number of worker threads.
.TP
.BI --timeout " SECONDS"
Set request timeout.
.TP
.B --fingerprint
Detect probable CMS, framework, infrastructure, or custom stack before the scan.
.TP
.B --waf-detect
Passively detect probable WAF or anti-bot protections.
.TP
.B --waf-safe-mode
Automatically switch to a cautious scan profile after WAF detection.
.TP
.B --header-bypass
Probe blocked 401/403 paths with controlled header-injection bypass variants.
.TP
.BI --reports " TYPES"
Write reports. Supported types include std, txt, json, csv, html, and sqlite.
.TP
.B --version
Show current version.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic directory scan:
.B opendoor --host https://example.com
.TP
Use a custom wordlist:
.B opendoor --host https://example.com --wordlist paths.txt
.TP
Read targets from a file:
.B opendoor --hostlist targets.txt
.TP
Read targets from standard input:
.B cat targets.txt | opendoor --stdin
.TP
Run WAF-safe scan:
.B opendoor --host https://example.com --waf-safe-mode --timeout 60 --retries 5
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/opendoor/opendoor.conf
Default OpenDoor configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/share/opendoor/data/
Runtime dictionaries and example transport profiles.
.SH HOMEPAGE
.UR https://github.com/stanislav-web/OpenDoor
.UE
